# ============================================================================
# üîí SECURITY: VITE_ PREFIX PATTERN
# ============================================================================
# CRITICAL: Understanding which variables use VITE_ prefix
#
# ‚úÖ VITE_ PREFIX (Public - bundled into client JavaScript):
#    - VITE_SUPABASE_URL
#    - VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#    - VITE_APP_* (app configuration)
#    - VITE_DEBUG_* (development flags)
#
# ‚ùå NO VITE_ PREFIX (Private - server-side only):
#    - ALL API KEYS (OpenRouter, OpenAI, Perplexity, etc.)
#    - ALL SECRETS (Supabase service role, Reddit client secret, etc.)
#    - ALL AUTHENTICATION TOKENS
#
# WHY: Vite bundles any variable with VITE_ prefix into the client-side
# JavaScript bundle, making it publicly accessible. API keys MUST be accessed
# only from Supabase Edge Functions (server-side) where they remain secure.
#
# MIGRATION: All API calls are being migrated to use the ai-proxy Edge Function
# which securely handles API keys server-side and proxies requests safely.
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# SYNAPSE SUPABASE CONFIGURATION (NEW PROJECT - MUST CREATE FIRST)
# ============================================================================
# 1. Create new Supabase project at: https://supabase.com/dashboard
# 2. Go to: Settings ‚Üí API
# 3. Copy your project URL and keys below

# ‚úÖ PUBLIC - Safe to expose in client bundle (used for Supabase client initialization)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_anon_key_here

# ‚ùå PRIVATE - Server-side only (never expose to client)
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_service_role_key_here
SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD=your_database_password_here

